Description: Comprehensive forensic triage collection. Superset of KapeTriage and SANS_Triage with Active Directory, DPAPI, WMI MOF files, and Recycle Bin data files. Collects file system artifacts, registry hives, event logs, ETL traces, execution evidence, browser data, scheduled tasks, SRUM, SUM, WMI repository, DPAPI keys, NTDS.dit, thumbnail cache, USB device logs, Windows Timeline, and more.
Author: Bradley Roughan
Version: 1.0
Id: 8a1b2c3d-4e5f-6789-0abc-def123456789
RecreateDirectories: true
Targets:
    #
    # === Antivirus & Security ===
    #
    -
        Name: Antivirus
        Category: Antivirus
        Path: Antivirus.tkape
    #
    # === Logs (Event Logs + ETL + PowerShell + Firewall + USB) ===
    #
    -
        Name: CombinedLogs
        Category: Logs
        Path: CombinedLogs.tkape
    #
    # === Evidence of Execution (Prefetch, Amcache, RecentFileCache, Syscache) ===
    #
    -
        Name: EvidenceOfExecution
        Category: Execution
        Path: EvidenceOfExecution.tkape
    #
    # === File System ($MFT, $LogFile, $J, $SDS, $Boot, $T) ===
    #
    -
        Name: FileSystem
        Category: FileSystem
        Path: FileSystem.tkape
